args:
After the first bout with Shishimai, Ieyasu and
Botan get in an argument where she attempts
to make him step down from his position of
leadership and restore their old friendship.
When it doesn't work, she storms off in a huff,
forcing the others to track her down.
We're backâ€”and we made a KILLING!
These New Year's gifts are pretty great.\nTalk about the perfect way to start a\nyear off right!
Shishimai and I could not be happier\nthat you enjoyed the proceedings.
Forgive me, but is it really all right for us\nto take this much?
Of course. You earned it by the sweat\nof your own brows.
Master Ieyasu cooked up this game so\nyou might accept his gifts more easily,\nafter all.
That's just how Master Ieyasu rolls when it\ncomes to hospitality!
So hey, what was that you did earlier\nwhen you suddenly grew larger?
Oh, that? Yeah, I can't carry the basket full\nof gifts if I don't get big.
So I had Amaterasu cast a spell that lets\nme get real big on the Kagura Stage.\nPreeeeetty amazing, right?!
What is this Amaterasu's story, anyway?\nShe seems to have a nearly limitless\nsupply of talents.
She's, like, the hugest and most\ndistinguished dragon of Hinomoto.
Yes, I figured that part out already.
Right? I mean, she gave you so many\nNew Year's gifts that you couldn't even\ncarry 'em without growing!
Hey, not to change the subject or anything,\nbut how'd it go between Addis and Botan?
Welp, it looks like the winners were\n{player_name} and his crew!
Which means THOSE two ended in a draw.
We SPECIFICALLY did this in order to\ndetermine a winner and loser.
The result is the result. Accept it with\ngrace, Botan.
Besides, what really matters is how much\nour new friends are enjoying themselves.
Victory and defeat are secondary to the\nsatisfaction we provide through our gift\nof hospitality.
Beating YOU is what's important to me!\nIt's all that MATTERS!
I don't understand, Botan. Why are you so\ndead-set on defeating Ieyasu?
Because I want him to step down from\nleading his Wyrmclan, okay?!
If I provided better hospitality than Ieyasu,\nit would mean he failed at his mission,\nright? I'm sure he'd resign after that.
Someone who would abandon his friends\nhas no place as a Wyrmclan leader.
It is as she says: The day I became a\nWyrmclan leader, I ended our friendship.
To be honest, I never expected us to be\ntalking like this again.
Yeah, but here we are. So why?!\nWhy did you DO THAT TO ME?!
Is it because I'm just some commoner?\nBecause our social positions are different?
If that's the case, make me a guard like\nthose other toadies who serve you!
I have no intention of employing you.\nNot you. Not ever.
Do you think I'm weak?!\nBecause I'm not!
Oh man, she is STEAMING.\nShould we go after her?
But are you certain you are all right with\nleaving things unsaid in this way?
Why are you so distant with Botan, Ieyasu?
I thought you were happy to have a\nchildhood friend that didn't treat you\nlike some kind of nobleman.
How can you now use that same social\nstanding to cast her aside?
If she were to be at my side, she would\ncome to regret it above all else.
Thus, before something truly regrettable\nhappened, I judged it better for both of\nus to end the relationship.
You don't think the two of you could\novercome that regret together?
I mean, you can't be happy seeing her\nso upset, can you?
Your Highness, we should hurry after her.
She's right. Hell, that crazy kid might\ndecide to charge a fiend nest again!
Ah, but she is a handful. I must be certain\nto give her a stern lecture once we are\nfinally able to track her down.
Very wellâ€”I shall attempt to locate Botan.\nWill you aid me in this?
Of course we will! Let's all split up\nand start looking for her.
Just you wait! I'll kill a million of you\nand PROVE that I'm strong!
I bet it'd be different if I were from a\nmilitary family like Sazanka...
Then I'd be able to serve you...
I hate that we can't be friends because of\nwhere we happened to be born...
Owww... Oh man, I didn't think there were\nfiends THAT big in this forest.
Uh oh. Looks like I'm surrounded.\n...Fine then. Let's do this!
Because I am NOT gonna lose!
I'm so glad we found you.
What are you two doing here?
Let us speak later. Right now, there is\nsome cleanup we must attend to.
How many of these fiends did you intend\nto fight today, Botan?
Let's use the dragon's power and take\ncare of this fast.
I was of the same mind, my friend.\nMarishiten, grant me your power!
